.TH SINGINE-ACTIVITY 1 "2026-03-15" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine\-activity \- inspect, instantiate, and evaluate activity taxonomy entries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine activity
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B singine activity list
[\fB--domain\fR \fIDOMAIN\fR] [\fB--json\fR|\fB--edn\fR|\fB--xml\fR]
.PP
.B singine activity inspect
\fIACTIVITY_ID\fR [\fB--json\fR|\fB--edn\fR|\fB--xml\fR]
.PP
.B singine activity run
\fIACTIVITY_ID\fR [\fB--input\fR \fIEDN_MAP\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine activity score
\fIOUTCOME_ID\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B activity
command works with the singine activity taxonomy: a strict classification
of actions, policies, and outcomes centred on the ultimate metric.
.PP
Every activity in the taxonomy follows the three-part structure:
.TP
.B Activity
Template that defines what is to be done and under which Policy.
.TP
.B Policy
Execution algorithm: applies rules to a context map and governs the action.
Governance decisions are recorded with
.BR singine-decide (1).
.TP
.B Outcome
Measured result carrying usage value, business value, and platform cost.
The derived score is:
.IP
.nf
usage_cost_benefit_score = usage_value + business_value \- platform_cost
.fi
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
Print all activities in the taxonomy.
Filter by domain with
.BR --domain .
.TP
.B inspect
Print the full definition of a single activity by ID.
.TP
.B run
Instantiate and execute an activity.
Accepts an EDN context map via
.B --input
to override defaults.
.TP
.B score
Print the usage-cost-benefit score for a completed outcome.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --domain \fIDOMAIN\fR
Filter activities to a single domain (e.g.
.IR emacs-orgmode-logseq ,
.IR elia-electricity ,
.IR data-production ).
.TP
.B --json
Emit raw JSON output.
.TP
.B --edn
Emit Clojure EDN output (default for JVM consumers).
.TP
.B --xml
Emit XML output compatible with the Elia electricity domain model.
.TP
.B --input \fIEDN_MAP\fR
EDN context map overrides for the
.B run
command, e.g.
.IR "{:env \"dev\"}" .
.SH TAXONOMY FILE
The canonical EDN taxonomy is at:
.IP
.I singine/core/resources/singine/activity/taxonomy.edn
.PP
It is the single source of truth from which XML, SPARQL, GraphQL,
LaTeX, SVG, and Logseq query artefacts are generated via:
.IP
.nf
singine xml matrix --db /tmp/sqlite.db --output-dir /tmp/singine-xml-matrix
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine activity list
singine activity list --domain emacs-orgmode-logseq --edn
singine activity inspect activity-emacs-logseq-01 --xml
singine activity run activity-dpdp-01 --input '{:env "dev"}'
singine activity score <outcome-uuid>
.fi
.SH DP(DP) — DATA PRODUCTION OF DATA PRODUCTION
The
.I data-production
domain contains the DP(DP) meta-activities: activities that govern the
activity taxonomy itself.  The logo is published at
.IR sina.khakbaz.com/img/dpdp-logo.svg .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1),
.BR singine-decide (1),
.BR singine-model (1),
.BR singine-xml (1),
.BR singine-bridge (1)
